<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="15" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[701,1228,213,1336]" pageId="15" pageNumber="15">
REMARKS: 
<taxonomicName authority="Chopra, 1923" authorityName="Chopra" authorityYear="1923" box="[847,1170,600,623]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Argeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lowisi">
<emphasis box="[847,997,600,623]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="15">Argeia lowisi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Chopra, B." box="[1007,1170,600,622]" pageId="15" pageNumber="15" pagination="411 - 550" refId="ref51130" refString="Chopra, B. 1923. Bopyrid isopods parasitic on Indian Decapoda Macrura. Records of the Indian Museum 25: 411 - 550, pls. 11 - 21." type="journal article" year="1923">Chopra, 1923</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Shiino, 1958" authorityName="Shiino" authorityYear="1958" box="[701,1014,629,652]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Stegoargeia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nierstraszi">
<emphasis box="[701,721,630,651]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="15">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[739,854,630,651]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="15">nierstraszi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Shiino, S. M." box="[865,1014,629,652]" pageId="15" pageNumber="15" pagination="27 - 74" refId="ref58507" refString="Shiino, S. M. 1958. Note on the bopyrid fauna of Japan. Report of the Faculty of Fisheries, Prefectural University of Mie 3: 27 - 74, pl. 3." type="journal article" year="1958">Shiino, 1958</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, do not belong in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1852" box="[701,777,660,681]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Argeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[701,777,660,681]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="15">Argeia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Females of both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1852" box="[1008,1172,660,681]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Argeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pugettensis">
<emphasis box="[1008,1028,660,681]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="15">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1048,1172,660,681]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="15">pugettensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Markham" authorityYear="1977" box="[701,847,689,712]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Argeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atlantica">
<emphasis box="[701,721,690,711]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="15">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[748,847,689,712]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="15">atlantica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have an oostegite 1 with a rounded (not tapered) posterior lobe, the first 5 pleomeres with lateral plates and a pair of uniramous pleopods on pleomeres 1–5. However, females of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chopra" authorityYear="1923" box="[903,1006,808,831]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Argeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lowisi">
<emphasis box="[903,923,809,830]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="15">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[942,1006,808,831]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="15">lowisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shiino" authorityYear="1958" box="[1074,1228,809,830]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Stegoargeia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nierstraszi">
<emphasis box="[1074,1094,809,830]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="15">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1114,1228,809,830]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="15">nierstraszi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
both have an elongate and tapered oostegite 1 posterior lobe (similar to that seen in 
<taxonomicName authority="Chopra, 1923" authorityName="Chopra" authorityYear="1923" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Stegoalpheon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kempi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="15">Stegoalpheon kempi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Chopra, B." box="[914,1082,898,920]" pageId="15" pageNumber="15" pagination="411 - 550" refId="ref51130" refString="Chopra, B. 1923. Bopyrid isopods parasitic on Indian Decapoda Macrura. Records of the Indian Museum 25: 411 - 550, pls. 11 - 21." type="journal article" year="1923">Chopra, 1923</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
), no lateral plates or biramous pleopods. Although the oostegite 1 is very similar in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chopra" authorityYear="1923" box="[1028,1126,956,979]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Argeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lowisi">
<emphasis box="[1028,1048,957,978]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="15">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1063,1126,956,979]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="15">lowisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shiino" authorityYear="1958" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Stegoargeia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nierstraszi">
<emphasis box="[1141,1161,957,978]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="15">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="15">nierstraszi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[776,780,988,1009]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="15">,</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chopra" authorityYear="1923" box="[835,931,986,1009]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Stegoalpheon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kempi">
<emphasis box="[835,851,987,1008]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="15">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[864,931,986,1009]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="15">kempi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the presence of five or six pairs of uniramous lateral plates and five pairs of biramous pleopods in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chopra" authorityYear="1923" box="[1005,1109,1046,1069]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Stegoalpheon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kempi">
<emphasis box="[1005,1021,1047,1068]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="15">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1041,1109,1046,1069]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="15">kempi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
precludes the inclusion of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chopra" authorityYear="1923" box="[888,988,1076,1099]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Argeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lowisi">
<emphasis box="[888,908,1077,1098]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="15">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[924,988,1076,1099]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="15">lowisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shiino" authorityYear="1958" box="[1047,1197,1077,1098]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Stegoargeia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nierstraszi">
<emphasis box="[1047,1067,1077,1098]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="15">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1083,1197,1077,1098]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="15">nierstraszi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in that genus. Therefore, we erect 
<emphasis box="[1087,1227,1106,1127]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="15">
<taxonomicName authority="An &amp; Boyko &amp; Li, 2015" authorityName="An &amp; Boyko &amp; Li" authorityYear="2015" box="[1087,1223,1106,1127]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Stegoargeia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">Stegoargeia</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[701,786,1136,1157]" pageId="15" pageNumber="15" rank="genus">n. gen.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<typeStatus box="[808,858,1136,1157]" pageId="15" pageNumber="15">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Chopra, 1923" authorityName="Chopra" authorityYear="1923" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Argeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lowisi">
<emphasis box="[965,1119,1135,1158]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="15">Argeia lowisi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Chopra, B." pageId="15" pageNumber="15" pagination="411 - 550" refId="ref51130" refString="Chopra, B. 1923. Bopyrid isopods parasitic on Indian Decapoda Macrura. Records of the Indian Museum 25: 411 - 550, pls. 11 - 21." type="journal article" year="1923">Chopra, 1923</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
), for the 
<typeStatus box="[870,919,1166,1187]" pageId="15" pageNumber="15">type</typeStatus>
species as well as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shiino" authorityYear="1958" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Stegoargeia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nierstraszi">
<emphasis box="[1139,1159,1166,1187]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="15">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="15">nierstraszi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The hosts for both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1852" box="[1019,1095,1196,1217]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Argeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1019,1095,1196,1217]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="15">Argeia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species are crangonids, while those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chopra" authorityYear="1923" box="[1023,1173,1224,1247]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Stegoalpheon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1023,1173,1224,1247]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="15">Stegoalpheon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[701,842,1255,1276]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="15">
<taxonomicName authority="An &amp; Boyko &amp; Li, 2015" authorityName="An &amp; Boyko &amp; Li" authorityYear="2015" box="[701,837,1255,1276]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Stegoargeia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">Stegoargeia</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[852,935,1255,1276]" pageId="15" pageNumber="15" rank="genus">n. gen.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, are alpheids. The males of all three genera are very similar and suggest a close relationship between the genera.
</paragraph>
